Package Food

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConsoleApp
    A console interface based off of a Finite State Machine, with values of state representing different states in the FSM.
    Fitter
    Provides methods to compute best fitting meal given a knapsack and nutrient target.
    Food
    The Food class is an ADT that represents a food item by its id, descriptor, and nutritional values.
    GroupInfo
    Class for importing the information for food groups from the CSV files
    GroupName
    ADT for a GroupName object
    Insertion
    The Insertion class provides methods to perform various different types of insertion sort.
    Knapsack
    Module to handle construction of, and interface with, Knapsack object.
    Meal
    Handles construction of and exported method for Meal ADT.
    NutrientInfo
    Provides an interface for looking up inforation about nutrients from their ID.
    NutrientTarget
    Contains information about goals for nutrient values as and ADT.
    NutriName
    Contains information about a given Nutrient Type as a NutriName ADT.
    PrefixTree
    Module Interface: public void insertFood(Food food) insert a food into the prefix tree (inserts the TAGS into the tree, not the food itself) public void insertTag(Food food,String tag) insert a tag into the prefix tree public Food[] getFood(String tag) returns a list of foods based on the word that is searched
    ReadCSV
    Class for importing CSV files from the 2015 Health Canada data on food nutritional values, and storing these values in an array of Food ADT objects.
    TimSort
    A class that implements TimSort.
    TimSortTest
